  <h2 id="explosion-proof">Explosion Proof Diesel Centrifuges (Class 1 Div 2)</h2>

  <p>
    For hazardous area installations, we offer <a href="/explosion-proof-centrifuge/">Class 1, Division 2 certified</a> diesel centrifuge systems. These systems use explosion-proof motors, certified control panels, and approved wiring methods suitable for areas where flammable vapors may be present.
  </p>

  <p>
    C1D2 systems are commonly required for fuel tank farms, marine engine rooms, and petroleum storage facilities.
  </p>

  <h2 id="workboat">Diesel Purification on Workboats</h2>

  <p>
    Smaller manual-clean centrifuges (DMB series) are popular for <strong>workboat and marine diesel purification</strong>. These compact units operate in confined engine rooms, providing continuous fuel polishing from the storage tank to the day tank.
  </p>

  <p>
    Marine applications benefit from the centrifuge's ability to handle the water ingress common in marine fuel systems &mdash; something filters alone cannot address.
  </p>

